
## 📌 Lab Objective

As part of an AWS data migration project, the Nautilus DevOps team required an S3 bucket to be provisioned using Terraform.

The goal was to create a private S3 bucket in AWS with public access completely blocked.

---

# 🏗️ Scenario

Organizations migrating workloads to AWS often need secure cloud storage for:

- Application data
- Backups
- Logs
- Migration files
- Archives

Instead of manually creating resources through the AWS Console, DevOps teams use Terraform to define infrastructure as code.

This allows infrastructure to be:

- Version controlled
- Reproducible
- Auditable
- Automated

