# 🔐 Security Concepts Learned

## Why Block Public Access?

An S3 bucket can accidentally become exposed through:

- Public ACL permissions
- Bucket policies
- Misconfigured permissions

AWS Public Access Block provides an additional security layer.

---

# 🧠 Key Learnings

- Terraform allows infrastructure to be managed through code.
- AWS resources can be recreated consistently across environments.
- S3 security requires more than simply creating a bucket.
- Public Access Block prevents accidental data exposure.
- Terraform resources can depend on each other automatically.

